      • invokeAtTargetRequestSending

        void invokeAtTargetRequestSending(HTTPCarbonMessage carbonMessage)
        Invoked when the request is started sending to the backend.
        Parameters:
        carbonMessage - sent request (i.e the message is already had started to send to backend) So no message body will be available. Even though the headers and properties are available, manipulating them won't change the request send to the back end (because the headers are already been send to the backend)
